&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that this vacancy is available for both Allied Health Professions and Nursing and Midwifery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Designated Clinical Officer (DCO) Special Educational Needs and Disability (SEND)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sunderland CCG is pleased to invite applications for a permanent Band 8a Designated Clinical Officer (DCO) Special Educational Needs and Disability (SEND) position.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The SEND Designated Clinical Officer (DCO) will lead the support to Sunderland CCG and Together for Children to ensure that they meet their statutory duties for children and young people, aged 0 – 25 years, with special educational needs and disability. The post holder will act as a strategic and operational lead for the Education, Health and Care Plan Pathway in accordance with the Children’s and Families Act 2014. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will ensure that the outcomes for CYP aged 0-25 with disabilities and those with SEN are maximised by working to improve quality of life, mental and physical health problems, personal autonomy and community inclusion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will be working within the Sunderland area and will need to be able to work effectively with a range of partnerships, including statutory services, voluntary and third sector agencies, parents, carers and children and young people.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you feel you have demonstrable experience in delivering against this agenda and the personality and commitment to integrate well, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We reserve the right to close the application process at any time based on the number of applications received.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Kimm Lawson &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Head of Integrated Commissioning for Children&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;07500102445 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Given the current Government Guidelines on Coronavirus and social distancing requirements, the ability to work from home is the CCG’s preferred position at the current time. This may change going forward. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
